<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?><?Xpress productLine="ncc-clause" ?><clause xmlns:xt="urn:xpressauthor:trackchanges" id="_16a67f19-8668-4c60-9855-6b7e9a373233" outputclass="ncc-clause"><meta><facet building="Class 1a"/><facet building="Class 1b"/><facet building="Class 10a"/><facet building="Class 10b"/><facet building="Class 10c"/></meta><sptc>E3D4</sptc><title id="_b989e49e-6ba4-4518-b60c-240c04fc4043">Warning against use of lifts in fire</title><archive-num><xt:delText xt:action="start" xt:author="Patrick Kerrigan" xt:dateTime="2024-03-12T09:25:00" xt:id="e9d43a10-d056-4571-bc3f-66bf4db8fbd0"/>2019: E3.3<xt:delText xt:action="end" xt:id="e9d43a10-d056-4571-bc3f-66bf4db8fbd0"/></archive-num><subclause id="_a8d63003-194e-4ec7-95e5-6c4009dc14b1" outputclass="subclause"><title id="_2e802795-835e-4df5-a9f9-341ad82c2b9d">SubClause</title><num>1</num><p>A warning sign must be displayed where it can be readily seen near every call button for a passenger lift or group of lifts throughout a building.</p></subclause><subclause id="_c4c2250c-8662-4a01-825a-c8fbcba64b14" outputclass="subclause"><title id="_724c6fa4-f078-4f2f-b5b6-d52217f52460">SubClause</title><num>2</num><p>The requirements of (1) do not apply to a small lift such as a dumb-waiter or the like that is for the transport of goods only.</p></subclause><subclause id="_29a1bacc-7dba-4ea6-ab1a-bc41d9febc8b" outputclass="subclause"><title id="_6712caf1-8f8b-40dd-a396-4d11673b7a47">SubClause</title><num>3</num><p>Each warning sign <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/5e2c1f63-e589-4ce1-95e8-5c3e286a7aff/1432_4.0.0.xml#_af6fde9f-147d-4782-8b85-42044e80fd42" id="_13d33398-b74f-4656-aea7-de89d2e8956e" scope="local" type="abcb-glossentry">required</xref> by (1) must comply with the details and dimensions of <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/5e2c1f63-e589-4ce1-95e8-5c3e286a7aff/256_0.9.0.xml#_dfbbf7bb-f6f1-45b2-abd8-02e72a8f7a13" id="_8d588dba-f6db-4da5-800e-49afcb25873a" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="image-reference">Figure E3D4</xref> and consist ofâ€”</p><ol outputclass="alpha"><li id="_da310964-d773-4755-8a6e-605f158db372">incised, inlaid or embossed letters <xt:insText xt:action="start" xt:author="Patrick Kerrigan" xt:dateTime="2024-03-12T09:21:00" xt:id="0e871197-3218-4730-a0a4-9737489de50f"/>in a colour contrasting with the background <xt:insText xt:action="end" xt:id="0e871197-3218-4730-a0a4-9737489de50f"/>on a metal, wood, plastic or similar plate securely and permanently attached to the wall; or</li><li id="_2edee8b6-13af-48ab-997e-460c128541ce">Letters <xt:insText xt:action="start" xt:author="Patrick Kerrigan" xt:dateTime="2024-03-12T09:24:00" xt:id="1f842c6e-75a6-4ce7-8f35-2bcd43a3ccd6"/>in a colour contrasting with the background <xt:insText xt:action="end" xt:id="1f842c6e-75a6-4ce7-8f35-2bcd43a3ccd6"/>incised or inlaid directly into the surface of the material forming the wall.</li></ol></subclause><image-reference conref="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/5e2c1f63-e589-4ce1-95e8-5c3e286a7aff/256_0.9.0.xml" id="_dfbbf7bb-f6f1-45b2-abd8-02e72a8f7a13"><num/><title id="_aca42ebf-dd6e-4794-9e52-d73648e10742"/></image-reference></clause>